In [33]:
def combine_rles(sample_rles, sample_class):
    combine_sample_rles = []
    j = 0
    for i in range(4):
        if i + 1 in sample_class:
            combine_sample_rles.append(sample_rles[j])
            j += 1
        else:
            combine_sample_rles.append("")
    return combine_sample_rles

def build_masks(rles, input_shape):
    depth = len(rles)
    height, width = input_shape
    masks = np.zeros((height, width, depth))
    for i, rle in enumerate(rles):
        if type(rle) is str:
            masks[:, :, i] = rle2mask(rle, (width, height))
    return masks

def rle2mask(mask_rle, shape=(256, 1600)):
    """
    mask_rle: run-length as string formated (start length)
    shape: (width,height) of array to return
    Returns numpy array, 1 - mask, 0 - background

    """
    s = mask_rle.split()
    starts, lengths = [np.asarray(x, dtype=int) for x in (s[0:][::2], s[1:][::2])]
    starts -= 1
    ends = starts + lengths
    img = np.zeros(shape[0] * shape[1], dtype=np.uint8)
    for lo, hi in zip(starts, ends):
        img[lo:hi] = 1
    return img.reshape(shape).T


def check_result(file):
    sample_filename = file
    
    sample_image_df = predict_csv[predict_csv['ImageId'] == sample_filename]
    sample_path = f"test_images/{sample_image_df['ImageId'].iloc[0]}"
    sample_img = cv2.imread(sample_path)
    print(sample_path)
    
    sample_rles = sample_image_df['EncodedPixels'].values
    sample_class = sample_image_df['ClassId'].values
    combine_sample_rles = combine_rles(sample_rles, sample_class)
    sample_masks = build_masks(combine_sample_rles, input_shape=(256, 1600))
    
    test_image_df = test_csv[test_csv['ImageId'] == sample_filename]
    test_rles = test_image_df['EncodedPixels'].values
    test_class = test_image_df['ClassId'].values
    combine_test_rles = combine_rles(test_rles, test_class)
    test_masks = build_masks(combine_test_rles, input_shape=(256, 1600))
    
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(9, figsize=(12, 12))
    axs[0].imshow(sample_img)
    axs[0].axis('off')
    for i in range(4):
        axs[i + 1].imshow(sample_masks[:, :, i])
        axs[i + 1].axis('off')
    for i in range(4):
        axs[i + 5].imshow(test_masks[:, :, i])
        axs[i + 5].axis('off')
    plt.show()
